White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki announced that her colleague Karine Jean-Pierre will be the next White House Press Secretary, making her the first Black woman and first openly LGBTQ+ person to serve in the role. Psaki praised Jean-Pierre's qualifications and experience in politics and advocacy. Psaki also provided updates on other topics, including the seizure of a Russian oligarch's yacht, the nomination of Steve Dettelbach to lead the ATF, and President Biden's upcoming trip to Cincinnati. She emphasized the administration's commitment to protecting women's reproductive rights and discussed potential executive actions on the issue. Psaki also addressed questions about the Supreme Court, the economy, immigration, and other topics.